properties.Name: LegalEntityForm
properties.Description:
A categorization of Legal Entities based upon common legal or operating characteristics, attributes or functions performed.

Larger commercial Legal Entities buy in larger quantities and therefore are offered different credit terms than individuals.   Therefore, it is important to know what type of Legal Entity you are dealing with in establishing credit terms and performing collection activities.

Commercial Legal Entities are also more complex and difficult to analyze.

It may be important to analyze financial statements and business ratios in determining their credit worthiness.

Ex. (US):  
Partnership 
Limited partnership (LP) 
Limited liability partnership (LLP) 
Limited liability limited partnership (LLLP) 
Limited liability company (LLC) 
Limited company (Ltd.) 
Not-for-profit corporation 
Sole proprietorship 
Trust company

Within a country the specific type of legal entity form may be defined.
